08:09.155 --> 08:11.449
Mm, dork but slimier.

08:11.449 --> 08:12.826
I thought
that was going well.

08:12.826 --> 08:15.578
Yes, well, I have only
known him for six days, so...

08:15.578 --> 08:18.123
I think we will
all get over it.

08:18.123 --> 08:19.666
I'm gonna go take a walk.

08:19.666 --> 08:22.627
[upbeat tropical music playing]

08:22.627 --> 08:23.712
EDWIN:
Hey, guys.

08:23.712 --> 08:25.839
Des, you got one for me?

08:25.839 --> 08:27.882
[chuckles]

08:27.882 --> 08:29.759
What's up your ass today, man?

08:29.759 --> 08:35.765
♪ ♪

08:35.765 --> 08:37.934
BERY:
Gogo, come here.

08:40.019 --> 08:44.941
Stephen saw Julian out
last night with another man.

08:44.941 --> 08:47.736
He minutes working here
be numbered.

08:47.736 --> 08:50.030
Poor Julian,
just being himself.

08:50.030 --> 08:52.365
Serves he right.
He's so obvious.

08:52.365 --> 08:53.908
[scoffs]
Well, now you're gonna end up

08:53.908 --> 08:55.827
having to carry
all his slack today.

08:55.827 --> 09:02.459
♪ ♪

09:02.459 --> 09:07.005
<i>SINGER: [through headphones]
♪ I wanted to be like you ♪</i>

09:07.005 --> 09:10.216
<i>♪ I wanted every-- ♪</i>

09:11.593 --> 09:14.012
<i>BIGGIE: ♪ I got the chronic
by the tree, 'cause ♪</i>

09:14.012 --> 09:16.222
<i>♪ I love it when you call me
Big Poppa ♪</i>

09:16.222 --> 09:17.599
<i>♪ Throw your hands
in the air-- ♪</i>

09:17.599 --> 09:19.601
EDWIN:
Hello, hello, Miss.

09:19.601 --> 09:20.685
ALISON: Hi.
EDWIN: [chuckles]

09:20.685 --> 09:23.021
Here you are again.

09:23.021 --> 09:25.273
Since when you listen
to music like that?

09:25.273 --> 09:27.275
<i>BIGGIE: ♪ I love it
when you call me Big Poppa ♪</i>

09:27.275 --> 09:30.028
ALISON:
I love hip-hop.

09:30.028 --> 09:31.446
Where he from, then?

09:31.446 --> 09:34.908
Since you're
such a big fan, right?

09:34.908 --> 09:36.284
He from New York,

09:36.284 --> 09:39.287
the greatest city
in the world, your home.

09:39.287 --> 09:41.080
You know, I have
a cousin who live there.

09:41.080 --> 09:43.082
He live in Queensbridge.

09:43.082 --> 09:45.251
You ever been Queensbridge?

09:45.251 --> 09:47.295
Maybe, yeah.
I-I think so.

09:47.295 --> 09:48.755
It's cool.

09:48.755 --> 09:52.008
Ever since he moved there,
I knew I could do it, too.

09:52.008 --> 09:54.052
What's it like?

09:54.052 --> 09:56.096
It's amazing.

09:56.096 --> 10:00.558
I mean, I live more,
like, city-adjacent,

10:00.558 --> 10:04.062
but I-I take the train in
all the time for the culture...

10:04.062 --> 10:05.480
nightlife.

10:05.480 --> 10:07.065
It's fun.

10:07.065 --> 10:09.901
You like culture?

10:09.901 --> 10:12.695
I do. G--

10:12.695 --> 10:14.364
- [chuckles]
- I love theatre

10:14.364 --> 10:16.032
- and restaurants...
- Mm.

10:16.032 --> 10:17.992
And traveling.

10:17.992 --> 10:20.036
Mm, one sunny resort
after another.

10:20.036 --> 10:24.499
That's not true!
[laughter]

10:24.499 --> 10:27.836
We went to Rome last year.

10:27.836 --> 10:29.504
[both chuckling]

10:29.504 --> 10:31.005
Okay.

10:31.005 --> 10:33.299
You know, this island,
we have culture, you know?

10:33.299 --> 10:34.884
We have culture.
We have tradition.

10:34.884 --> 10:37.637
We have everything
as old and as deep as Italy.

10:37.637 --> 10:39.764
You have never even left
the hotel.

10:39.764 --> 10:41.683
Show me, then. I--

10:41.683 --> 10:45.895
I would love to see
what your island has to offer.

10:45.895 --> 10:48.439
I-I want to experience
all of it.

10:48.439 --> 10:50.358
Ooh, all of it?

10:50.358 --> 10:53.319
Yeah, it'd be cool
to lime with you after work.

10:53.319 --> 10:54.696
Hmm.

10:54.696 --> 10:55.989
Oh, you want to lime?

10:55.989 --> 10:59.200
You want to become
like a native now, right?

10:59.200 --> 11:00.910
Tell you what, Miss.

11:00.910 --> 11:02.745
I don't think
you can handle it.

11:04.622 --> 11:07.667
Well, how can I convince you?

11:07.667 --> 11:11.129
Mm, um...

11:11.129 --> 11:13.006
- I can't.
- No ideas?

11:13.006 --> 11:14.174
EDWIN:
No, no, no, no, no.

11:14.174 --> 11:15.925
Why don't you--
Give it--give it a go.

11:15.925 --> 11:17.302
Why don't you try?

11:17.302 --> 11:21.472
<i>[soft music]</i>

11:21.472 --> 11:24.601
[panting]

11:24.601 --> 11:26.936
Oh, hey.
[door closes]

11:28.354 --> 11:30.690
Don't you have that deposition?
What are you doing back?

11:30.690 --> 11:32.942
It's 10:00 a.m.
Why aren't you at work?

11:32.942 --> 11:35.445
I, um...

11:35.445 --> 11:37.739
[sighs]
I got fired.

11:37.739 --> 11:40.408
You got fired?

11:40.408 --> 11:42.452
When?

11:42.452 --> 11:44.621
Last night.

11:44.621 --> 11:46.539
Why'd you get fired?

11:47.624 --> 11:50.752
Well, I, uh, didn't hand
the cut in on time.

11:52.378 --> 11:53.963
I got sidetracked.

11:56.382 --> 11:58.218
JOSH:
[sighs]

12:06.184 --> 12:07.352
CLAIRE:
Josh.

12:09.604 --> 12:12.023
Are you seeing someone?

12:12.023 --> 12:13.316
CLAIRE: What?

12:13.316 --> 12:15.818
I ran into him, you know,
the cab driver,

12:15.818 --> 12:18.404
the one who walked you
to the door.

12:18.404 --> 12:21.824
Saw him at the restaurant
where you bought the, uh...

12:21.824 --> 12:24.452
the plantains.

12:24.452 --> 12:25.745
CLAIRE:
You think I'm--

12:25.745 --> 12:27.664
I'm having an affair
with a cab driver,

12:27.664 --> 12:29.457
because, what,
we both like plantains?

12:29.457 --> 12:31.084
Don't do that.

12:31.084 --> 12:33.711
You've been lying to me...

12:33.711 --> 12:35.505
for so long,

12:35.505 --> 12:40.093
and I've tried to let you
sort it all out on your own,

12:40.093 --> 12:44.138
but, um--
but I can't take it anymore.

12:44.138 --> 12:46.099
Josh, Josh, please.

12:46.099 --> 12:48.017
Josh, I need you!

12:48.017 --> 12:50.436
Yes, I haven't been letting
you in, but I want to.

12:50.436 --> 12:52.272
I want to tell you everything.

12:52.272 --> 12:53.272
Okay?

12:53.272 --> 12:55.274
I will tell you everything.

12:57.151 --> 12:58.778
Tonight.

12:58.778 --> 13:01.114
We're supposed to have dinner
with your parents tonight.

13:01.114 --> 13:03.157
Oh, fuck!

13:03.157 --> 13:05.410
Josh, stop, please.

13:05.410 --> 13:07.078
Look at me.

13:07.078 --> 13:10.081
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

13:10.081 --> 13:12.500
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:12.500 --> 13:15.420
I would never--
never cheat on you...

13:18.047 --> 13:19.465
Ever.

13:19.465 --> 13:21.843
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:21.843 --> 13:23.261
I promise.

13:25.680 --> 13:27.265
I love you.

13:27.265 --> 13:34.314
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:34.314 --> 13:36.316
[door closes]

13:36.316 --> 13:39.902
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:43.489 --> 13:46.492
<i>[soft music]</i>

13:46.492 --> 13:50.538
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:50.538 --> 13:51.873
SUSAN:
Mia.

13:53.541 --> 13:55.126
- Hi.
- Hi, Susan.

13:55.126 --> 13:57.462
Oh, it's--
it's so good to see you.

13:57.462 --> 13:59.422
And, Clairey,
look how big you've gotten.

13:59.422 --> 14:02.175
[chuckles]
I'm just here stocking up.

14:02.175 --> 14:04.719
Molly's home
from her first year of school.

14:04.719 --> 14:06.721
Oh, Molly.
How is she?

14:06.721 --> 14:10.141
She--she was just devastated

14:10.141 --> 14:12.393
to hear about Alison, Mia.

14:12.393 --> 14:14.729
We--we all were.

14:14.729 --> 14:17.315
If you need anything,
we're here for you.

14:17.315 --> 14:18.608
Just call.

14:18.608 --> 14:20.359
I really appreciate that.

14:20.359 --> 14:22.570
Thank you, and I will.

14:22.570 --> 14:25.114
- It was nice to see you, Susan.
- You too.

14:25.114 --> 14:26.115
MIA:
Okay.

14:28.367 --> 14:29.660
[sighs] Okay.

14:38.211 --> 14:41.214
[scanner beeping]

14:46.552 --> 14:49.555
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

14:49.555 --> 14:55.436
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:55.436 --> 14:57.313
MIA:
[softly] Okay. It's okay.

14:57.313 --> 15:01.442
[beeping continues]

15:01.442 --> 15:04.779
BILL: Have you read
the coroner's report?

15:04.779 --> 15:06.197
No. So...
[sighs]

15:06.197 --> 15:08.991
So do
the background checks again.

15:08.991 --> 15:10.159
No, I-I won't accept that.

15:10.159 --> 15:12.203
I will--
I will never accept that.

15:12.203 --> 15:14.330
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:14.330 --> 15:16.541
How many times do I have to
go through this with you guys?

15:16.541 --> 15:18.793
It's--it's been
six fucking months.

15:18.793 --> 15:20.169
Fuck!

15:20.169 --> 15:27.176
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:30.596 --> 15:32.515
Grocery store?
MIA: Yeah.

15:34.058 --> 15:36.811
I talked to my sister.

15:36.811 --> 15:39.397
[sighs]

15:39.397 --> 15:42.108
She offered to take Claire
to Paris for the month.

15:42.108 --> 15:43.109
Mm, no.

15:45.862 --> 15:47.572
I want her here with us.

15:47.572 --> 15:51.033
MIA: I--
Bill, the fucking tabloids,

15:51.033 --> 15:52.410
the TV--

15:52.410 --> 15:56.873
she can't keep hearing
this stuff about her sister.

15:56.873 --> 15:58.833
BILL:
Her sister's dead, Mia.

15:58.833 --> 16:01.085
There's nothing
we can do to change that.

16:01.085 --> 16:03.087
MIA:
Her tic's getting worse.

16:03.087 --> 16:06.424
She's just a little girl,
and we have to protect her.

16:06.424 --> 16:13.431
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:15.683 --> 16:17.852
CLAIRE:
That is so fun.

16:17.852 --> 16:19.228
MIA:
Ooh.

16:19.228 --> 16:21.189
Oh, hey!

16:21.189 --> 16:23.274
You seem energized.

16:23.274 --> 16:25.067
Good walk?

16:25.067 --> 16:27.069
ALISON: Great walk.
MIA: Oh, good.

16:27.069 --> 16:28.446
Listen...

16:28.446 --> 16:31.490
