big scavenger hunt later.

16:31.490 --> 16:34.493
Should I sign us up?

16:34.493 --> 16:35.703
No, I'm in the mood

16:35.703 --> 16:37.955
for something
a little more exciting.

16:37.955 --> 16:40.499
MIA: Okay, well, what were
you thinking, sweetie?

16:42.668 --> 16:46.255
I think we should go
off the resort.

16:46.255 --> 16:47.590
MIA: Well...

16:50.051 --> 16:53.679
I could see if they have
those whale-watching tours.

16:53.679 --> 16:55.890
You remember the one
we did in Saint Martin?

16:55.890 --> 16:59.685
CLAIRE: I love whales!
ALISON: No.

16:59.685 --> 17:04.106
No, it needs to be specific
to the indigenous culture.

17:04.106 --> 17:05.733
CLAIRE: What's that?

17:07.318 --> 17:09.737
ALISON: I'll be right back.
I have an idea.

17:11.113 --> 17:13.157
MIA:
Just so you know,

17:13.157 --> 17:15.993
I'm never letting you
go to college.

17:15.993 --> 17:18.371
[laughter]

17:18.371 --> 17:19.872
EDWIN:
Mm-mm, mm-mm, mm-mm,

17:19.872 --> 17:22.041
Gogo, why you--why you
shaking up drinks, man?

17:22.041 --> 17:24.001
Your head up you ass?
Julian been fired.

17:24.001 --> 17:25.461
- EDWIN: For what?
- You know for what.

17:25.461 --> 17:27.713
EDWIN: Oh, can't keep
the cocks out of he mouth?

17:27.713 --> 17:29.590
But, shit, Go, we a man down--

17:29.590 --> 17:31.300
Oh, no, we an anti-man down.

17:31.300 --> 17:33.511
Gogo, should I get
the beer myself?

17:33.511 --> 17:34.720
- GOGO: No, no.
- I can see it.

17:34.720 --> 17:37.139
EDWIN: Des, Des,
come give Gogo a hand, come.

17:37.139 --> 17:38.349
DESMOND:
I'll give you some more.

17:38.349 --> 17:40.101
EDWIN: He be slammed here.
Come give a hand.

17:40.101 --> 17:44.146
I gonna give two hands,
because Gogo be my friend.

17:44.146 --> 17:45.731
Okay, good for you.

17:45.731 --> 17:48.276
You see,
I be a true friend to he.

17:50.152 --> 17:51.779
Are you high?

18:13.759 --> 18:16.137
You okay?

18:16.137 --> 18:18.639
I still feel like a prick.
OLIVIA: You'll bounce back.

18:18.639 --> 18:21.767
I mean, find someone who's--
like, who gets you, you know,

18:21.767 --> 18:23.602
and just, like, wants to be
around you and stuff.

18:23.602 --> 18:25.771
TYLER: I apologized.

18:25.771 --> 18:27.398
I didn't mean to--

18:27.398 --> 18:29.025
It's not even
about you, you know.

18:29.025 --> 18:31.986
Edwin just makes for
a better story for Alison...

18:31.986 --> 18:33.821
to take back
to Princeton with her.

18:33.821 --> 18:35.531
- Wait, what?
- What?

18:36.616 --> 18:37.950
Alison's with Edwin?

18:37.950 --> 18:39.535
I don't--
I don't think I said that.

18:39.535 --> 18:42.413
I, uh, um...

18:42.413 --> 18:45.416
Okay.
Tyler, I'm so sorry. I--

18:45.416 --> 18:48.711
Just--if anybody asks,
I didn't say anything, okay?

18:52.131 --> 18:53.674
BERY: I can't believe
you got my doing this.

18:53.674 --> 18:54.800
DESMOND:
Sorry.

18:54.800 --> 18:56.135
BERY: You know
I'm a babysitter, right?

18:56.135 --> 18:57.803
DESMOND: Yeah. No, Stephen
need to pay us more.

18:57.803 --> 18:59.138
[both chuckle]

18:59.138 --> 19:01.599
Look, um, Bery...
BERY: [chuckles]

19:01.599 --> 19:04.518
DESMOND: Um, can I talk to you
about Edwin?

19:04.518 --> 19:06.145
BERY: Yeah, sure.
DESMOND: [grunts]

19:06.145 --> 19:08.397
ALISON: Hey, Desmond--
[sighs]

19:08.397 --> 19:11.442
My family and I would love
to see more of the island.

19:11.442 --> 19:12.735
DESMOND:
Oh, sure.

19:12.735 --> 19:14.654
You want to do, like,
a snorkeling excursion

19:14.654 --> 19:16.072
or a ziplining tour or someth--

19:16.072 --> 19:18.616
ALISON: No, something
not silly and touristy.

19:18.616 --> 19:20.576
Like, do you have something
more authentic?

19:20.576 --> 19:23.496
Ah, perhaps,
like a restaurant for dinner?

19:23.496 --> 19:25.623
I have the perfect place.
Look, my friend Jeanne run it.

19:25.623 --> 19:27.458
All the local people
frequent there.

19:27.458 --> 19:28.834
ALISON: Yes, amazing.
DESMOND: You know?

19:28.834 --> 19:30.753
I'll sort out
all the transportation for you,

19:30.753 --> 19:32.838
and you just need
to be there, yeah?

19:32.838 --> 19:35.216
7:00?
DESMOND: 7:00 works fine.

19:35.216 --> 19:37.843
Thank you. Bye.

19:37.843 --> 19:39.095
DESMOND:
[sighs]

19:39.095 --> 19:41.097
BERY: What did you want
to talk to me about?

19:44.225 --> 19:45.851
Um...

19:47.436 --> 19:48.938
[sighs]

19:48.938 --> 19:52.733
You ever notice anything
between Edwin and Sara?

19:52.733 --> 19:57.113
Like--like, maybe he have
feelings for her?

19:57.113 --> 19:59.281
No.
No way.

19:59.281 --> 20:01.117
DESMOND:
Yeah, it's just I...

20:01.117 --> 20:05.413
I saw something yesterday,
and it made me feel so weird.

20:06.914 --> 20:08.582
Sara's with Keithley,

20:08.582 --> 20:10.918
and Edwin
would not do that to Gogo.

20:10.918 --> 20:12.586
They be best mates.

20:12.586 --> 20:15.047
[scoffs]
What be wrong with you?

20:17.258 --> 20:19.468
- DESMOND: [grunts]
- You owe me after this.

20:19.468 --> 20:21.220
DESMOND: Yes, ma'am.
BERY: Thank you.

20:22.680 --> 20:25.891
[siren wailing, horn honking]

20:25.891 --> 20:28.894
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

20:28.894 --> 20:35.943
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:43.951 --> 20:45.953
[door bells jingle]

20:45.953 --> 20:52.918
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:00.009 --> 21:03.012
<i>[person speaking
native language on TV]</i>

21:03.012 --> 21:10.019
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:34.168 --> 21:36.170
GOGO:
[sighs]

21:36.170 --> 21:42.676
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:42.676 --> 21:44.970
Ben.

21:44.970 --> 21:47.348
Who did it?
Who ransacked my room?

21:47.348 --> 21:49.350
It was Farhad.
GOGO: Why?

21:50.559 --> 21:52.978
He thinks
you stole his money.

21:52.978 --> 21:54.605
What money?

21:54.605 --> 21:56.357
BEN:
Cash under his bed.

21:56.357 --> 21:58.818
He was saving
for his mother's surgery.

22:00.236 --> 22:02.404
I wouldn't take that.

22:02.404 --> 22:06.033
He says you did,
and he's looking for payback,

22:06.033 --> 22:08.244
so be careful.

22:08.244 --> 22:10.621
Seriously, Clive...

22:10.621 --> 22:13.624
he's not in his right head
over this.

22:13.624 --> 22:20.589
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:20.589 --> 22:22.591
[perfume sprays]

22:25.010 --> 22:27.388
- [door opens]
- Oh, hey.

22:27.388 --> 22:29.306
[door closes]
You're here. Um...

22:29.306 --> 22:32.601
They're on their way over.

22:32.601 --> 22:33.936
What?

22:35.604 --> 22:37.606
So, uh...

22:37.606 --> 22:41.735
you've been, uh, hanging out
with Clive Richardson?

22:41.735 --> 22:43.654
It's not--
JOSH: Don't.

22:43.654 --> 22:46.073
No more lying.

22:46.073 --> 22:48.617
Just got off the phone
with Sunita--I know everything.

22:53.080 --> 22:54.832
Okay, Josh.

22:54.832 --> 22:57.042
I didn't mean to lie to you.

22:57.042 --> 23:00.254
I just didn't know how...

23:00.254 --> 23:01.714
how to tell you--

23:01.714 --> 23:03.799
That you have been sitting
down to dinner

23:03.799 --> 23:05.801
with the man
who killed your sister?

23:05.801 --> 23:07.261
You realize
how dangerous that is?

23:07.261 --> 23:08.429
What the fuck
are you thinking?

23:08.429 --> 23:09.638
This is why
I didn't say anything,

23:09.638 --> 23:11.098
because I knew
you would overreact!

23:11.098 --> 23:12.683
I knew you would
try and stop me!

23:12.683 --> 23:14.643
Of course
I would try to stop you.

23:14.643 --> 23:16.604
Anybody in their right mind
would try to stop you!

23:16.604 --> 23:18.188
Oh, so I'm not
in my right mind?

23:18.188 --> 23:20.691
I didn't say that.
[doorbell buzzes]

23:20.691 --> 23:23.694
CLAIRE:
[breathes sharply]

23:23.694 --> 23:25.904
[sighs]

23:25.904 --> 23:28.532
My parents.

23:28.532 --> 23:30.117
JOSH:
Look, if...

23:30.117 --> 23:32.119
Don't worry--I'm not gonna say
anything to them.

23:32.119 --> 23:33.495
Just...

23:33.495 --> 23:36.916
they can't know
about any of this...

23:36.916 --> 23:39.460
[plastic bag rustles]
Obviously.

23:46.967 --> 23:49.094
I don't want to go out
to dinner.

23:50.888 --> 23:53.682
ALISON: Come on, Clairey,
it'll be so fun.

23:53.682 --> 23:56.894
We'll learn all about how
people live here firsthand.

23:56.894 --> 23:58.896
But what
if the goat woman's there?

23:58.896 --> 24:01.940
ALISON: No, the goat woman
lives on Faraway Cay...

24:01.940 --> 24:04.318
nowhere near where we're going.
[hair dryer whirring]

24:04.318 --> 24:05.903
I think
I just want to stay here

24:05.903 --> 24:07.696
and have chicken fingers again.

24:07.696 --> 24:09.156
Claire, you're being a baby.

24:09.156 --> 24:12.743
Maybe we should just have
dinner here, Al, yeah?

24:12.743 --> 24:15.204
Silver lining--
less chance of food poisoning.

24:15.204 --> 24:16.747
Do you hear
how gross you sound?

24:16.747 --> 24:18.958
MIA: Al, calm down.
It's not that big of a deal.

24:18.958 --> 24:20.709
ALISON: It's "Alison,"
and it is a big deal,

24:20.709 --> 24:22.795
and you guys
don't do her any favors

24:22.795 --> 24:25.130
when you baby her like this.

24:25.130 --> 24:28.509
Your life is going
to be extremely boring

24:28.509 --> 24:31.720
if all you do is sit in pools,
eating chicken fingers.

24:31.720 --> 24:34.723
[door opens, closes]

24:34.723 --> 24:37.726
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

24:37.726 --> 24:40.854
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:40.854 --> 24:43.565
DESMOND: Guys, look,
just come this way.

24:43.565 --> 24:46.443
Guys, come this way
for the real plantains, yes?

24:46.443 --> 24:49.530
My friend Ramon here--he's
gonna show you a fine time.

24:49.530 --> 24:52.866
It's gonna be lovely, man.
EDWIN: [scoffs, chuckles]

24:52.866 --> 24:55.369
The queen from the land Westchester

24:55.369 --> 24:59.289
finally leave the hotel
in a giant resort bus.

24:59.289 --> 25:01.583
That's some real island culture
there, huh?

25:01.583 --> 25:05.212
Good job, miss.
[laughs]

25:05.212 --> 25:08.382
Big man.

25:08.382 --> 25:10.592
Oh, Miss Alison, right on time.

25:10.592 --> 25:12.553
Hey, um...

25:12.553 --> 25:15.431
Claire, my sister,
she's--she's not feeling well,

25:15.431 --> 25:17.725
so we're gonna
have to sit this one out.

25:17.725 --> 25:19.226
I'm sorry.

25:19.226 --> 25:21.186
Thank you.

25:23.897 --> 25:26.775
PAUL: Ugh, finally,
a moment away from Jamie.

25:26.775 --> 25:29.194
I can't help it.
It's like I enjoy her

25:29.194 --> 25:31.196
and all her neuroses.

25:31.196 --> 25:32.448
We came on this trip

25:32.448 --> 25:34.241
so that we could spend
more time together,

25:34.241 --> 25:37.661
but we've barely had a meal
just the two of us.

25:37.661 --> 25:40.330
GREG:
Hey, I have an idea.

25:40.330 --> 25:42.291
Yesterday
that hot bartender, Julian,

25:42.291 --> 25:44.001
told me about a little place
on the island.

25:44.001 --> 25:45.794
PAUL:
Mm-hmm.

25:45.794 --> 25:49.089
You maybe want to get
a little naughty tonight?

25:49.089 --> 25:50.799
Could be an adventure.

25:50.799 --> 25:53.010
- Huh?
- I say hell yes.

25:53.010 --> 25:55.137
GREG:
Yes, adventure time!

25:55.137 --> 25:57.431
- To adventure time.
- Let's do it. To adventure.

25:57.431 --> 25:59.058
I love you.
GREG: Love you.

26:01.852 --> 26:03.771
DESMOND:
[spits, snorts]

26:03.771 --> 26:09.777
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:09.777 --> 26:11.487
Fuck.

26:13.405 --> 26:15.407
[exhales deeply]

26:15.407 --> 26:21.371
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:21.371 --> 26:23.165
Let me ask you
a question, yeah?

26:23.165 --> 26:26.418
Let me ask you a question.

26:26.418 --> 26:28.378
What do Goges mean to you?

26:28.378 --> 26:31.048
What the fuck kind
of question is that, then?

26:31.048 --> 26:33.759
I'm onto you, mate.

26:35.469 --> 26:37.554
What the--what the fuck, Des?

26:37.554 --> 26:39.264
STEPHEN:
Chitchat time is over.

26:39.264 --> 26:40.849
We're a man down.

26:40.849 --> 26:47.898
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:00.702 --> 27:02.329
EDWIN: Stephen want to know
where I go,

27:02.329 --> 27:04.122
tell him
I had enough for today.

27:04.122 --> 27:05.499
But, Edwin, it's a madhouse.

27:05.499 --> 27:07.876
EDWIN: Gogo,
I got shit to take care of.

27:07.876 --> 27:10.087
I should just Sharpie

27:10.087 --> 27:11.880
"clueless white woman"
on my forehead.

27:11.880 --> 27:13.507
Stop.
You're amazing.

27:13.507 --> 27:17.302
No one thinks that of you,
and especially Edwin, right?

27:20.055 --> 27:21.890
Um, shit, okay.

27:21.890 --> 27:23.976
Hey, so you're gonna be
really mad at me,

27:23.976 --> 27:26.228
and I'm--ugh, I'm so sorry,

27:26.228 --> 27:28.480
but, um, uh, before,

27:28.480 --> 27:30.232
I did something
kind of terrible.

27:30.232 --> 27:32.526
I told Tyler about
the whole Edwin situation.

27:32.526 --> 27:34.361
- I'm really sorry.
- Is he pissed?

27:34.361 --> 27:36.154
He's pissed, right?
OLIVIA: A little bit.

27:36.154 --> 27:38.073
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
I'm sorry.

27:44.580 --> 27:46.540
Can we have a sec?

27:46.540 --> 27:49.918
Yeah, yeah.
Um, I'll go.

27:54.923 --> 27:56.133
TYLER: Hey.

27:56.133 --> 27:57.593
Hey.

27:57.593 --> 28:00.637
Can I, uh,
ask you a question?

28:00.637 --> 28:04.474
Are you and Edwin,
like, serious?

28:06.351 --> 28:09.354
I'm here
for, like, one more day.

28:09.354 --> 28:10.564
No.

28:10.564 --> 28:13.609
But are you sleeping
with him?

28:13.609 --> 28:15.819
That's none of your business.

28:17.779 --> 28:20.324
I'm sorry.
It's just...

28:22.409 --> 28:24.620
I'm trying to understand.

28:24.620 --> 28:26.204
I'm not.

28:26.204 --> 28:28.624
Okay?
I'm not.

28:28.624 --> 28:30.083
Okay.

28:31.585 --> 28:33.962
But///

28:33.962 --> 28:36.173
are you going to?

28:36.173 --> 28:38.383
I know how that sounds.

28:39.760 --> 28:42.179
But I'm asking as a friend.

28:42.179 --> 28:43.972
[chuckling]
Okay.

28:43.972 --> 28:45.098
"A friend."

28:46.975 --> 28:50.771
Why the fuck do you think
you're so special?

28:50.771 --> 28:52.439
Edwin hooks up
with another girl

28:52.439 --> 28:55.067
every set of vacationers,
so, like...

28:55.067 --> 28:57.819
you're just his white girl
of the week.

28:57.819 --> 28:59.529
That's not true.

28:59.529 --> 29:01.323
TYLER: [scoffs]
Have you asked him?

29:01.323 --> 29:08.330
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:11.458 --> 29:14.419
ALISON: [sobbing]
[door closes]

29:14.419 --> 29:21.426
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:37.693 --> 29:39.695
[scoffs]

29:41.279 --> 29:44.116
[breathes deeply]

29:44.116 --> 29:47.119
[toilet flushes]

29:48.870 --> 29:50.831
Oh, I'm so sorry.

29:53.291 --> 29:56.003
This is so embarrassing.
[sniffles]

29:59.840 --> 30:02.009
You okay?

30:05.262 --> 30:08.181
ALISON:
Can I ask you a question?

30:08.181 --> 30:10.350
Am I generic?

30:11.852 --> 30:14.730
I'm sorry.
You know...

30:14.730 --> 30:17.315
You don't know me,

30:17.315 --> 30:19.317
but I am...

30:21.611 --> 30:23.905
For the record.

30:23.905 --> 30:25.866
But I-I've--

30:25.866 --> 30:29.453
I've watched you, and I...

30:29.453 --> 30:31.121
I can see...

30:33.331 --> 30:35.667
You're the kind of person
who commands attention.

30:35.667 --> 30:38.712
You know?
You--you...

30:38.712 --> 30:41.840
you've got o-opinions, brains.

30:41.840 --> 30:44.051
You're special.

30:44.051 --> 30:46.053
You think that?

30:47.554 --> 30:51.516
[chuckles]
[softly] Thank you.

30:51.516 --> 30:55.103
You're really nice.
[chuckles, sniffles]

30:56.730 --> 30:58.899
You're gonna be a great mom.

30:58.899 --> 31:01.568
[sniffles]

31:01.568 --> 31:03.570
[sighs]

31:07.574 --> 31:10.577
[door opens, closes]

31:15.290 --> 31:16.958
BILL: So tell us more.
How was the food?

31:16.958 --> 31:18.960
CLAIRE: Aunt Cynthia
made me eat a snail.

31:18.960 --> 31:20.796
I hated it.
BILL: [laughing]

31:20.796 --> 31:21.880
And the Louvre?

31:21.880 --> 31:23.757
CLAIRE: It was crowded
and noisy.

31:23.757 --> 31:25.383
BILL: [chuckles]
CLAIRE: And I missed you.

31:25.383 --> 31:27.094
MIA:
Oh, we missed you, too, honey.

31:27.094 --> 31:28.929
What do you want for dinner?
I can make tacos.

31:28.929 --> 31:32.766
BILL: Ooh, Taco Tuesday. Hmm?
[both chuckle]

31:32.766 --> 31:35.435
You seem different
from before.

31:35.435 --> 31:37.437
MIA:
Well, honey,

31:37.437 --> 31:39.314
we're...

31:39.314 --> 31:42.317
trying to...

31:42.317 --> 31:43.693
be better.

31:43.693 --> 31:46.613
But are you better?
BILL: Oh, Clairey.

31:46.613 --> 31:49.407
It's called
"faking it till you make it."

31:49.407 --> 31:52.494
We're gonna try and be okay,
and eventually we will be.

31:52.494 --> 31:54.037
You'll see.

31:54.037 --> 31:57.624
MIA:
Daddy and I were talking...

31:57.624 --> 32:01.962
and we were thinking
that it could be fun

32:01.962 --> 32:05.173
for the three of us
to make a fresh start.

32:06.383 --> 32:07.801
What do you mean?

32:07.801 --> 32:10.971
What do you think
about us moving somewhere...

32:10.971 --> 32:12.514
a place like California?

32:12.514 --> 32:15.183
But why?

32:15.183 --> 32:17.853
Well, we think
it might be a good idea

32:17.853 --> 32:19.938
to go somewhere where...

32:21.231 --> 32:23.275
Where people
won't always bring up--

32:24.651 --> 32:26.444
Where we won't
always be reminded

32:26.444 --> 32:28.488
of the terrible thing
that happened to Alison.

32:28.488 --> 32:31.116
But, hey, hey, hey...

32:31.116 --> 32:34.244
only if you want to,
okay, honey?

32:37.038 --> 32:40.333
You don't want
to remember Alison?

32:40.333 --> 32:43.461
Oh, no, of course we do.
Of course.

32:43.461 --> 32:48.216
But it's also important that
we not be sad all the time.

32:48.216 --> 32:51.219
And, you know...

32:51.219 --> 32:53.847
I was thinking
that I might try gardening,

32:53.847 --> 32:57.475
and your dad was thinking
he might change his job

32:57.475 --> 32:59.186
and try teaching.

32:59.186 --> 33:01.188
And you know what?

33:01.188 --> 33:03.356
You could try new things, too.

33:03.356 --> 33:06.359
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

33:06.359 --> 33:09.446
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:09.446 --> 33:11.865
JOSH: As you can see, we still
need some pictures hung,

33:11.865 --> 33:14.492
got to get some plants,
but we're gettin' there.

